Job Summary

We are seeking a data analyst for a well established organization in the banking industry to help with their regulatory reporting projects.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering or Information Systems;
• At least 3 years of experience in data related projects and with data visualization, dashboard creation;
• Hands-on experience : Qlik Sense / Qlikview / Tableau;
• Proficient in SQL based querying of database for data analysis;
• Prior experience in banking;
• Knowledgeable in data analytics processes;
• Strong communication skills with an analytical mindset.

Desired Skill-set
• Prior experience in regulatory reporting, such as BCBS239 related work;
• Proficient in Informatica IDQ, QlikSense;
• Relevant Qliksense / Qlikview / Tableau Certification.

Responsibilities
• Understand business requirements and build BCBS239 rules;
• Create and upload manual templates for data quality processing;
• Conduct data quality checks;
• Build and... improve regulatory reporting dashboards and conduct monthly reporting;
• Manage stakeholders and provide training to business users on new reports and dashboards.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTEs website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

